{
  "stem": "1917.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 305.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we tried to go around the best-- I mean we were pretty happy most of the time until we had to deal with the news or with any kind of personal harassment.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Then by-- And the other thing was that my mother wanted to go and visit my grandmother and my grandfather and her brother.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And you could not travel without special permit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I think in the four years of occupation, maybe she got twice a permit to go, and we went to see our grandparents.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then, towards the end, of course, permit was never granted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Even I know on one occasion, my grandmother was quite ill, and my mother felt so badly that she could not go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And she was the only daughter to be with my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Things were getting, as I said, from bad to worse, and we could sense it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "There was no doubt about it, that things are going to be-- that it never seemed to improve.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Only-- and my mother became very ill in '43.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Late winter of '43, she developed typhoid.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "She was between life and death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So again, we needed somebody Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We couldn't have anybody from the village helping, because that was against the law.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father went to the city and hired a nurse to come and help take care of my mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was so fragile that she couldn't even turn from side to side.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she barely survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was very weak, still, in the-- in February, in March of '44 when we were ordered one day-- four Hungarian gendarmes came and said, pack food for two weeks.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We are taking you to a ghetto, so then could resettle you in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
